Print the following pattern for the given N number of rows.

Pattern for N = 3
 A
 BB
 CCC
 
Input format :
Integer N (Total no. of rows)

Output format :
Pattern in N lines

Constraints
0 <= N <= 26

Sample Input 1:
7

Sample Output 1:
A
BB
CCC
DDDD
EEEEE
FFFFFF
GGGGGGG

Sample Input 2:
6

Sample Output 2:
A
BB
CCC
DDDD
EEEEE
FFFFFF

CODE:-

import java.util.Scanner;
public class Solution{
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	    Scanner s = new Scanner (System.in);
	    int n = s.nextInt();
	    int i = 1;
	    while(i<=n){
	        int j = 1;
	        char ch = (char)('A' + i - 1);
	        while(j<=i){
	            System.out.print(ch);
	            j=j+1;
	        }
	        System.out.println();
	        i=i+1;
	    }
	}
}
